events.name: Boston Celtics at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Julius Randle and the New York Knicks will open the NBA playoffs at home.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle, Knicks beat Celtics to clinch No. 4 seed in East

headlines.description: — Oshae Brissett scored a career-best 31 points and Domantas Sabonis added 25 points, 16 rebounds and three steals and the Indiana Pacers beat the Toronto Raptors 125-113 to lock up the Eastern Conference’s ninth seed.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brissett has career-high 31 as Pacers beat Raptors 125-113

headlines.description: — The Washington Wizards finished eighth in the Eastern Conference standings and set up a play-in matchup against the No. 7 Boston Celtics by coming back to beat the Charlotte Hornets 115-110 Sunday with Bradley Beal scoring 20 of his 25 points in the...
headlines.shortLinkText: Wiz to face Celtics after beating Hornets for 8th in East

events.name: Phoenix Suns at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — E’Twaun Moore scored 22 points and made a 3-pointer with 2.2 seconds remaining that lifted the Phoenix Suns past the San Antonio Spurs 123-121 on Sunday and kept alive their chances at the No. 1 seed in the Western Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Moore, short-handed Suns hold off Spurs 123-121

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry became the oldest scoring champion since Michael Jordan at age 35 in 1998, finishing with 46 points as the Golden State Warriors held off the Memphis Grizzlies 113-101 on Sunday in a regular-season finale that determined the play-in...
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry is scoring champ, Warriors beat Grizzlies for 8 seed

headlines.description: — Rookie Onyeka Okongwu set career highs with 21 points and 14 rebounds, and the Atlanta Hawks headed to the playoffs on a roll with a 124-95 rout of the woeful Houston Rockets in the regular-season finale Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hawks head to playoffs after 124-95 rout of woeful Rockets

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant had 23 points, 13 assists and eight rebounds and the Brooklyn Nets took the No. 2 seed in the Eastern Conference by beating the Cleveland Cavaliers 123-109 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant, Irving power Nets past Cavs for No. 2 seed in East

headlines.description: — Tyrese Maxey had 30 points, seven rebounds and six assists, and the Eastern Conference champion Philadelphia 76ers beat the Orlando Magic 128-117 on Sunday night in a meaningless regular-season finale.
headlines.shortLinkText: Maxey leads 76ers past Magic 128-117 in meaningless finale

headlines.description: — Nemanja Bjelica scored 17 of his 21 points in the first half, and the Miami Heat routed the Detroit Pistons 120-107 on Sunday night despite holding out several key players in a relatively meaningless game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat rout Pistons 120-107 with several key players out

headlines.description: — Thaddeus Young scored 20 points, Coby White added 19 and the Chicago Bulls beat Milwaukee 118-112 with Giannis Antetokounmpo and the rest of the Bucks’ starters missing the regular-season finale Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young, White help Bulls top starter-less Bucks 118-112

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 30 points in his final audition for NBA Rookie of the Year, leading the Minnesota Timberwolves to a 136-121 victory over the postseason-bound Dallas Mavericks on Sunday night.

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — LeBron James scored 25 points before he appeared to mildly aggravate a right ankle injury and the Los Angeles Lakers closed out the regular season with a 110-98 victory over the New Orleans Pelicans on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: James scores 25, tweaks ankle, Lakers top Pelicans 110-98

events.name: LA Clippers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Rookie Aleksej Pokusevski scored a career-high 29 points, and the Oklahoma City Thunder defeated the Los Angeles Clippers 117-112 on Sunday night in the regular-season finale for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pokusevski scores 29, Thunder top Clippers in season finale

events.name: Denver Nuggets at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard had 22 points and 10 assists and the Portland Trail Blazers beat the Denver Nuggets 132-116 in the regular-season finale Sunday night to secure their eighth straight playoff berth, the longest active streak in the NBA.
headlines.shortLinkText: Blazers beat Nuggets 132-116, secure 6th seed for playoffs

headlines.description: — Jordan Clarkson scored 33 points, Rudy Gobert added 13 points and 16 rebounds and the Utah Jazz took the No. 1 spot in the NBA playoffs, beating the Sacramento Kings 121-99 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz take top spot in NBA playoffs, thump Kings 121-99
